There are 20 long words in the text.

The formula for the LIX readability score is:
 LIX = (N x 0.07) + (K x 0.011) + (S x 0.013)

Where N = number of long words, 
K = number of words per sentence, 
S = number of sentences (we'll use number of periods for this)

K (number of words per sentence) = 70 / 1 ≈ 70
but according to some sources we should use the average 25-30, so 
we can safely substitute with 30 (it doesn't significantly affect the final score but does eliminate the denominator=zero problem)

We have N, K and S: N = 20, K = 30, S = 1.

LIX = (20 x 0.07) + (30 x 0.011) + (1 x 0.013)
LIX ≈ 1.4 + 0.33 + 0.013
LIX ≈ 1.744

LIX ≈ 1.75